<h1 class="doc-page-title">Multiple selection</h1>

<p>
  Ember Power Select allows to select multiple options by just passing <code>multiple=true</code>
  to the component.
</p>

{{#code-sample as |component|}}
  <pre class="code-sample-snippet {{if (eq component.activeTab 'template') 'active'}}">
    \{{#ember-power-select options=names multiple=true as |name|}}
      \{{name}}
    \{{/ember-power-select}}
  </pre>
  <pre class="code-sample-snippet {{if (eq component.activeTab 'javascript') 'active'}}">
    export default Ember.Controller.extend({
      names: ['Stefan', 'Miguel', 'Tomster', 'Pluto']
    });
  </pre>
  <div class="code-sample-snippet result {{if (eq component.activeTab 'result') 'active'}}">
    {{#ember-power-select options=names multiple=true as |name|}}
      {{name}}
    {{/ember-power-select}}
  </div>
{{/code-sample}}

<p>
  When the multiple mode is enabled you will notice that there is no search box but instead
  you can type directly in the trigger to search. This is because you can use backspace to remove
  options and also there is optional support for adding more options with free text (thing about a
  component for add tags) but we will dive into that in another chapter.
</p>

<p>
  You can also use multiple selection with the blockless version of the component described in the
  {{#link-to 'docs.how-to-use-it'}}How to use it{{/link-to}} section.
</p>

<p>
  In the next page we're going to see how to disable the entire component or
  specific options of it.
</p>

